description:
## Severity
Critical
## Dimension
concurrency
## Location
src/subagent.rs:1312-1331 (execute_task_tool background path) and src/subagent.rs:688-689 (run_subagent registration)
## Violation
In `execute_task_tool` the background branch registers an agent and returns its id to the caller:

```rust
let agent_id = BACKGROUND_AGENTS.register(agent_type, description);
// ...
handle.spawn(async move {
    let result = run_subagent(&config_bg, &app_config_bg, &client_bg).await;
    if !result.success {
        BACKGROUND_AGENTS.fail(&agent_id_bg, result.output);
    }
});
```

But `run_subagent` itself unconditionally calls:

```rust
let id = BACKGROUND_AGENTS.register(config.agent_type, &config.task);
```

(line 689) producing a *second*, different id. All `increment_turns`, `finish`, and transcript storage inside `run_subagent` are keyed on that inner id; the caller-visible id is only ever touched on the `result.success == false` branch. The user is handed an `agent_id` that will report `turns=0`, no result, and is_finished=false forever, even after the agent completes successfully. `agent_output` cannot recover the real output.

## Mandated refactor
Make `run_subagent` accept an optional pre-allocated `agent_id` (or remove the inner `register` and require callers to register), so the id the caller sees is the id the subagent uses for tracking / transcript / finish. The background spawn path must not double-register.
## Filed from QA review dispatch
